<def f='linux-4.14.y/fs/xattr.c' l='872' ll='921' type='int simple_xattr_set(struct simple_xattrs * xattrs, const char * name, const void * value, size_t size, int flags)'/>
<doc f='linux-4.14.y/fs/xattr.c' l='858'>/**
 * simple_xattr_set - xattr SET operation for in-memory/pseudo filesystems
 * @xattrs: target simple_xattr list
 * @name: name of the extended attribute
 * @value: value of the xattr. If %NULL, will remove the attribute.
 * @size: size of the new xattr
 * @flags: %XATTR_{CREATE|REPLACE}
 *
 * %XATTR_CREATE is set, the xattr shouldn&apos;t exist already; otherwise fails
 * with -EEXIST.  If %XATTR_REPLACE is set, the xattr should exist;
 * otherwise, fails with -ENODATA.
 *
 * Returns 0 on success, -errno on failure.
 */</doc>
